# Next.js Frontend Conventions

## Tech Stack

- **Framework**: Next.js 14 (App Router)
- **UI**: shadcn/ui + TailwindCSS
- **Animations**: Framer Motion (subtle fade-in / slide-up via `SectionReveal`)
- **Icons**: lucide-react
- **Design tokens**: `design.json` → CSS variables

## Design System

All styling references CSS variables from `globals.css`, sourced from `design.json`:

```tsx
// ✅ Use CSS variables for all design tokens
className="bg-[var(--card)] text-[var(--text)] rounded-[var(--radiusCard)]"
style={{ boxShadow: 'var(--shadowCard)' }}

// ❌ Don't hardcode colors
className="bg-[#111827] text-[#F9FAFB]"
```

Key variables: `--bg`, `--card`, `--border`, `--primary`, `--primarySoft`, `--text`, `--textSecondary`, `--textMuted`, `--success`, `--radiusCard`, `--radiusButton`, `--radiusBadge`, `--shadowCard`, `--glowPrimary`, `--gap`, `--container`, `--cardPadding`.

## Component Patterns

- `CardShell` — reusable card with hover lift + glow, uses design tokens
- `SiteHeader` — sticky header with nav links
- Pages use `SectionReveal` wrapper for scroll animations
- Homepage is a card-grid layout (`grid-cols-12`)

## File Organization

- shadcn components: `src/components/ui/`
- Layout components: `src/components/layout/`
- Feature sections inline in page files or in `src/components/sections/`
